<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>JavaScript on Starslayerx' Blog</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/tags/javascript/</link><description>Recent content in JavaScript on Starslayerx' Blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://starslayerx.github.io/tags/javascript/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Part 1 - Fundamentals :01~05</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-part-1-fundamentals-01~05/</link><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-part-1-fundamentals-01~05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="21-hellow-wrold">2.1 Hellow Wrold&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Firtly, let&amp;rsquo;s see how to attach a script to a webpage.
For server-side environments (like Node.js), you can execute this script with a command like &lt;code>node my.js&lt;/code>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="the-script-tag">The &amp;ldquo;script&amp;rdquo; tag&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>JavaScript programs can be inserted almost anywhere into an HTML docuemnt using the &lt;code>&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;&lt;/code> tag&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-html" data-lang="html">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="cp">&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">html&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">body&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">p&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span> Before this script...&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">p&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">script&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="nx">alert&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s1">&amp;#39;Hello, World!&amp;#39;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">);&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">script&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">p&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>...After the script...&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">p&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">body&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">html&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>The &lt;code>&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;&lt;/code> tag contains JavaScript code which is automatically executed when the browser process the tag.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Part 1- Fundamentals :06~10</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-part-1-fundamentals-06~10/</link><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-part-1-fundamentals-06~10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="26-interaction-alert-prompt-confirm">2.6 Interaction: alert, prompt, confirm&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Will introduce &lt;code>alert&lt;/code>, &lt;code>prompt&lt;/code> and &lt;code>confirm&lt;/code> in this chapter.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="alert">alert&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>It shows a message and waits for the user to press &amp;ldquo;OK&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nx">alert&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;Hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">);&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="prompt">prompt&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>This function &lt;code>prompt&lt;/code> accepts two arguments&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nx">result&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">prompt&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">title&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">,&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">[&lt;/span>&lt;span class="k">default&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">]);&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>It shows a modal window with a text message, an input field for the visitor, and the buttons OK/Cancel.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;code>title&lt;/code>: The text to show the visitor.
&lt;code>default&lt;/code>: An optional second parameter, the initial value for the input field.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Part 1 - An Introduction</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-part-1-an-introduction/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-part-1-an-introduction/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="an-introduction-to-javascript">An Introduction to JavaScript&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Let’s see what’s so special about JavaScript, what we can achieve with it, and what other technologies play well with it.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="why-is-it-call-javascript">Why is it call JavaScript?&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>JavaScript initially called &amp;ldquo;Live Script&amp;rdquo;. But Java was popular at that time, so it was decided that positioning a new language as a &amp;ldquo;younger brother&amp;rdquo; of Java would help.
But as it evolved, JavaScript became a fully independent language with its won specification called &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript">ECMAScript&lt;/a>, and now it has no relation to Java at all.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>